title: Complete coverage: Colonial League boys cross country championship
text:
Notre Dame won the 11th Colonial League meet team boys cross country championship of coach Art Corriganâ€™s legendary career Wednesday afternoon at the league meet at DeSales University. 
But the Crusaders did not make it easy on themselves. 
Notre Dame edged past Southern Lehigh by just three points, 61-64, for the title. 
Palmerton senior Zach Svetik won the individual title in 17 minutes, 57 seconds. Northern Lehigh senior Gavin Kemery was second in 18:02.
